  <h2>Augusta Has a Strong Inventory of Older Homes</h2>
  <p>A lot of Augusta's housing stock dates back to the 1920s through 1960s. These homes have real character — craftsman details, big lots, mature trees — but they also carry the maintenance burden of their age. Electrical systems, plumbing, and roofs on homes this old require attention that owners don't always have the resources to address.</p>
  <p>Estate sales are common in Augusta. Longtime residents who have owned their homes for 40 or 50 years leave behind properties that need work before they're marketable. Heirs who live out of town or simply don't want a renovation project on their hands are a good fit for what we do.</p>
